ass=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Nov 14, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104paf1665702713868.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/paf1665702713868.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/paf1665702713868.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"paf1665702713868\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"paf1665702713868__compile_a_project_16729\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">To compile a project, click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> button. Compiling a\n      project, compiles all the development objects it references.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"paf1665702713868__li_d1427e1_d1428e1_d1429e1\">Open the project and click\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span>. <p class=\"p\" id=\"paf1665702713868__p_d3908e1_d3909e1_d3910e1\">Compilation\n               processing messages and results are displayed in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compiler\n                  Output</span> tab.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"paf1665702713868__li_d1430e1_d1431e1_d1432e1\">To compile individual objects in a project, select the\n            object, right-click and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile</span> from the context menu. For\n            components, you can also choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Compile &amp; Test</span>. <div class=\"note tip note_tip\" id=\"paf1665702713868__note_cmw_f1b_bzb\"><span class=\"note__title\">Tip:</span> You can also use shortcut keys\n                  <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">Ctrl+F7</kbd> to compile a current object and\n                  <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">Ctrl+Shift+F7</kbd> to compile and test a current\n            object.</div></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jwc1695725497353.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Adding user-defined keyboard shortcuts in the IDE</a><p>You can use the following default shortcut keys in the IDE to navigate inside the editor or trigger various supported actions with a keyboard, such as compile a current object or compile and test an object.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/spu1692183913093.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Projects</a><p>A project is a collection of references to main development objects. It is used to create and organize components, modeled entities, and libraries that are needed to build the application.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vwa1665702579295.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Compilation Process</a><p>Most editors have a Compile command that starts the compilation process. For some objects (such as components, services, global objects, and application shells), compilation results in compiled objects that can be used in the Uniface runtime environment. For other objects (such as IncludeScript), the compiler only checks the definition, syntax, and/or integrity.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530830\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530830\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Compile a Project Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Nov 14, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 To compile a project, click the Compile button. Compiling a project, compiles all the development objects it references. Open the project and click Compile . Compilation processing messages and results are displayed in the Compiler Output tab. To compile individual objects in a project, select the object, right-click and choose Compile from the context menu. For components, you can also choose Compile & Test . Tip: You can also use shortcut keys Ctrl+F7 to compile a current object and Ctrl+Shift+F7 to compile and test a current object. Related Links Adding user-defined keyboard shortcuts in the IDE You can use the following default shortcut keys in the IDE to navigate inside the editor or trigger various supported actions with a keyboard, such as compile a current object or compile and test an object. Projects A project is a collection of references to main development objects. It is used to create and organize components, modeled entities, and libraries that are needed to build the application. Compilation Process Most editors have a Compile command that starts the compilation process. For some objects (such as components, services, global objects, and application shells), compilation results in compiled objects that can be used in the Uniface runtime environment. For other objects (such as IncludeScript), the compiler only checks the definition, syntax, and/or integrity. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}